summary: This is a bank transaction record showing a mobile deposit credit of $16.95 to a Bank of America account, with a subsequent payment to Discover Bank. The document appears to be a routine financial record, possibly part of a larger set of financial documents related to the Epstein case.

events.title: Mobile Deposit Transaction
events.description: A $16.95 mobile deposit credit was processed to a Bank of America account, with a payment made to Discover Bank.

keyFacts: A financial transaction for $16.95 occurred on March 18, 2019.
The transaction involved a mobile deposit credit to Bank of America and a payment to Discover Bank in New Castle, Delaware.
The document is part of a financial records set related to the Epstein case investigation.
No named individuals are mentioned in this specific financial record.
The transaction appears routine with no immediately apparent connection to criminal activity.
